==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monetary
<hw>Mon"e*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monetarius</ets> belonging to a mint. See <er>Money</er>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to money, or consisting of money; pecuniary.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>monetary</xex> relations of Europe.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>E.
Everett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Monetary unit</b></col>, <cd>the standard of a national
currency, as the dollar in the United States, the pound in England, the
peso in Mexico, the ruble in Russia, the franc in France, the mark in
Germany. Also, the standard of an international currency, such as the
euro used in the European union.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moneth</ent>⟦br⟧
